<subSubSection pageNumber="265" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="265">Note:</emphasis>
Rather than treat this as an illegitimate replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1753)" authorityName="C. E. Hubb." authorityYear="1753" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Aegilops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="265">A. incurva</emphasis>
L. (1753)
</taxonomicName>
, it seems preferable to regard it as an orthographic variant. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Aegilops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incurvata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="265">Aegilops incurvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
included the elements originally included in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="265">Nardus articulata</emphasis>
L. (1753), the latter name having been placed into the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. E. Hubb." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Aegilops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="265">A. incurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Linnaeus in 1759.
</paragraph>
